observations.recommendation:
We recommended that the Management to:

a. Create an Inventory Committee, to take charge of the inventory taking of the PPEs of the Municipality;

b. Direct the Property Custodian to prepare the RPCPPE and reconcile the same with the records of the Municipal Accountant;

c.  The Municipal Accountant to prepare Journal Entry Voucher, to adjust the PPE account based on its accuracy, completeness and existence before the preparation of the annual Financial Statements of the succeeding years; and

d. Facilitate the implementation of the One-Time Cleansing of PPE in accordance with COA Circular No. 2020-006.

We recommended that the Management:

a.   Direct the Municipal Engineer and Municipal Planning and Development Officer to review and expedite execution of priority projects included in the Annual Investment Plan so that delay in the implementation thereof could be avoided and desired benefits may be derived accordingly; 

b.  Prepare a realistic and implementable plan, after taking into consideration all the technical aspects and funding requirements in the implementation, to avoid re – programming and to fast tract the project implementation;

c.  Direct the Municipal Budget Officer to accurately present in the Statement of Appropriation, Allotment and Obligation (SAAOB) the identified PPAs, particularly the reprogrammed PPAs to properly monitor the accuracy of obligations; and  

d. 	As much as practicable, avoid delegating implementation of the 20% development funds PPAs to Barangays, these barangays have their own 20% DF to attend to. Instead, the municipality should spearhead its execution to ensure that funds are efficiently utilized. Otherwise, revisit Memorandum of Agreement between the Municipality and Barangays and include sanction for the delayed implementation of projects.

We recommended that the Management:

a. direct the Municipal Treasurer to enforce remedies on collections of delinquent real property taxes as prescribed in Section 256 to 260 of the Local Government Code and/or formulate strategies and conduct tax campaigns;


b. instruct the Municipal Assessor to submit an updated Assessment Roll to the Municipal Treasurer’s Office,  to serve as their guide in the collection of RPT,  to keep their records updated and to monitor status of collection of current and delinquent taxpayers.

The following courses of action are recommended:

Submit the lacking documentary requirements;

2. Submit written explanations and/or justifications on why the violations were committed;
3. Avoid procuring goods that were not included in the APP and in the supplemental procurement plans; and,
Ensure that future procurement of land should be in accordance with the IRR of RA 10752.

Send demand letters to barangays for the immediate liquidation of the funds transferred to them;

Stop granting funds to barangays with unliquidated balances to the municipality; and,

Revise the MOA to be used for future fund transfers to barangays indicating therein the fixed date/period when to properly liquidate the funds transferred by the municipality.

Avail of the computerized system in handling the data of properties and taxpayers to generate reliable, complete, and certified list of real property tax collectibles and other reports;



Consistently post the notice of delinquency in compliance with the foregoing provision of the LGC; and

Exert utmost efforts for the collection of real property tax collectibles.

Refrain from granting additional cash advances to accountable officers whose previous cash advances were not yet liquidated;

Direct the accountable officers to strictly comply with the rules and regulations particularly on the liquidation of cash advances within the prescribed period to ensure that all disbursements are recorded in the books in the appropriate time/period;

Constantly monitor and remind all accountable officers to immediately liquidate their outstanding cash advances as soon as the purpose of such has already been served; and

Whenever applicable condition exists, request for write-off of dormant unliquidated cash advances which remained non-moving for 10 years or more and where settlement could no longer be ascertained in accordance with the guidelines and procedures provided under COA Circular No. 2016-005.

We recommended the following courses of action to avoid another loss in the operation in the ensuing years:

a.	allocate a full stub of official receipts in order to issue the same in a strict numerical sequence and monitoring of the receipts would be easy to accomplish;

b.	reduce the number of job order employees  to serve in the business in to three (3) to minimize operations cost;

c.	extend the time of accepting customers up to 10pm in the evening since it would mean additional income to the LGU;


d.	efficiently use electricity to cut costs; and maintain a separate  record for  the business enterprise to consequently monitor its operations.

