We recommended that Management:

To adhere to the guidelines set forth in Section 89 of PD 1445 and COA Circular no. 97-002 dated February 10, 1997;

To exert extra effort for the enforcement of liquidation of the said cash advances; 

To request for write-off for those AOs who were already dead and/or can no longer be traced and follow the guidelines set under COA Circular 2016-005 dated December 19, 2016.

We recommended to the Management that:

Instruct the Inventory Committee to exert more effort to complete the conduct of physical inventory of all PPE accounts;

A task force, composing of personnel from Accounting and GSO, be created to conduct the reconciliation of the affected accounts as soon as the physical count is complete;

The Accounting Office should prepare Journal Entry Vouchers to adjust reconciling items identified with sufficient and appropriate supporting documents;

The General Services Office exclude items with serviceable life of more than one year but small enough to be considered as PPE in accordance with COA Circular No. 2005-002 dated April 14, 2005.

We recommended that the Management: 

Procure common-use supplies at PS-DBM;

Attach certification of non-availability from PS-DBM for unavailable items procured to private suppliers;

Procurements of goods should be awarded to eligible suppliers or pre-selected qualified suppliers; and

Observe strictly the policies and procedures under the revised IRR of RA 9184 in the procurement of goods specially for common-use supplies with the benefits due them.

We recommended that management:

Instruct the Municipal Accountant to stop the practice of recording directly to expense account for advance payment for catering services;

Avoid erasures for every supporting documents to the claims;

Valid documentation only will be supported to the claims. If possible, pictures to be taken should indicate actual date the activity was conducted;

Invitation to Bid for catering services must be supported with the details of the activities to be conducted and the estimated amount required for every activity.

Submit justification on deficiencies noted.

We recommended that Management:

To set aside appropriation/funding for the Construction of Stockroom for Drugs and Medicines Storage;

To provide a temporary storage which is suitable for stocking room of drugs, medicines and other medical supplies that could protect from any element which can damage such inventories;

To use the birthing clinic solely for the purpose it was built;
To instruct the MHO to prepare monthly utilization and inventory report which shall be furnished to Accounting and General Services Office for monitoring purposes and accounting thereof; and 

To exert extra effort in safeguarding the drugs and medicines to prevent wastage of government funds.

We recommended that Management to:

Prepare Program of Work for the total amount allocated for the Rehabilitation of the Closed Dumpsite;

Stop the practice of utilizing the fund for the expenses not directly attributable to projects;

Fast track the implementation of the project;

Stop the practice of burning plastic bags and other alike materials which poses health hazards to the general public; and

Monitor the constructed MRF’s in different areas and barangays within the Municipality to see if the facility is operating effectively and its design followed the guidelines set by Section 33 of RA 9003 or the Ecological Solid Waste Management act of 2000.

