We recommend that Management:
Issue demand letters to all concerned parties to settle their outstanding cash advances immediately, otherwise, cause the withholding or suspension of salaries of officials and employees concerned for non-compliance therewith pursuant to COA Circular No. 97-002 and Section 89 of PD 1445;

No additional cash advance should be granted unless previous cash advance has been settled;

Enforce strictly the prescribed rules and regulations in handling cash advances and the rendering of accounts by the AOs concerned.

We recommend that management install control measures on travels by:

Regulating the travel and travel claims of officials and employees;

Stop the practice of allowing employees to reimburse actual travel expenses that are not absolutely necessary in the performance of their assignment;

Stop sending officials and employees to seminars, trainings and conventions which do not relate to their function;

List all the passengers in the trip tickets and

Designate liaison officers in every office on the submission of report

We recommend that Management:
Stop charging ineligible expenses to 5% LDRRMF;

Allocate funds for regular operation expenses of the LDRRM Office;

Instruct the Municipal Accountant to make adjusting entry for the purchases of hygiene kit; and

Follow strictly the regulation in the utilization of the 5% Local Disaster Risk Reduction and Management Fund as provided under Section 5.1 of the Joint Memorandum Circular No. 2013-1 of DBM and DILG dated March 25, 2013.

It is also recommended to maximize the utilization of the LDRRF allocation for disaster preparedness, prevention and mitigation and allocate funds for projects which can prevent/eliminate/lessen the flood risks so that greater number of its constituents can be benefited.

We recommended that management direct the MENRO to:

provide containers/receptacles which will be put in the public places and these containers must be properly marked or identified for on-site collections such as compostable, non-recyclable, recyclable, special waste and/or any other classifications as may be determined by the Municipal Solid Waste Management Board;
Closely monitor the proper segregation of solid waste disposal by every household and establishments collected at the Materials Recovery Facilities as temporary dumpsite.

Impose sanctions/penalties for every household and establishments which violated the proper segregation of solid waste;

Regularly inspect and maintain the cleanliness in the surroundings of the public places particularly in the market.

It is also recommended to mobilize the active participation of schools, private organization and barangay officials informing, educating and monitoring households in the proper waste disposal from source.

